The paper deals with the problem of detecting malicious behavior in security, which is a core issue in computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach uses adversarial reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the game-theoretic model used to capture the interaction between the defender and attacker, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a method for prioritizing alerts, which can be seen as a decision-making problem, and decision theory is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT).
